{"title":"Choppy — a light weight balance bike for kids that’s made of wood?","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/27/choppy-wooden-balance-bike/","date":1630076134000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div data-off-canvas-content=\"\"><main role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-269466\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><header></header><section itemprop=\"text\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134952/choppy-feat-2.jpg\"><figure><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1196\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134952/choppy-feat-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"Choppy wooden balance bike for kids on Indiegogo\" loading=\"eager\" data-feature=\"1\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><figcaption>all images c. SCHUM Inc./Indiegogo</figcaption></figure></a><p>If you’re looking for a first bike for your toddler, you have a new, lightweight option on the market. Choppy is a wooden balance bike for kiddos from one to four years of age. The company’s pitch is simple: toy-meets-tool, an active, engaging way to kickstart a toddler’s motor skills and stoke their sense of adventure.</p><h2>Choppy’s key features</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:740x493/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"Choppy wooden balance bike for kids on Indiegogo\" width=\"1200\" height=\"799\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2-768x511.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:740x493/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.3348207907235845\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26134955/choppy-2-768x511.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\"></a></p><p>The company behind this balance <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/05/new-fezzari-lone-peak-24-kids-mountain-bike-gets-a-shred-ready-build/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">bike for kids</a> puts an emphasis on convenience in several ways.</p><p>First, assembly. The bike’s assembly process is tool-free, and the brand prides itself on how much simpler it is than “putting together IKEA furniture.” Sure, that’s a low bar, but it’s not a terrible selling point.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"YouTube video player\" data-ezsrc=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/M4imPRvvJyg\" width=\"796\" height=\"448\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p><p>Second, long-term usability. The wooden balance bike is growth-spurt friendly thanks to its adjustable seat and handlebars.</p><p>Third, portability. The bike is quick and easy to dismantle. Once dissembled, Choppy condenses down neatly making it suitable for car travel.</p><h2>Wooden balance bike design</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1.jpg\" alt=\"choppy balance bike for kids chart\" width=\"1200\" height=\"847\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1-297x210.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1-800x565.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1-120x85.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1-768x542.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1-297x210.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1-800x565.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1-120x85.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/26135640/choppy-1-768x542.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>Notably, the built-out wooden balance bike is free from child-safety hazards like metal bearings, screws, and spokes. The saddle is ergonomically spring-mounted to cushion little jammer’s backsides from burly terrain.</p><p>Aldis Blicsons, the inventor behind Choppy, noted the bike is, “Probably the most lightweight children’s wooden balance bike.”</p><p>The build features birch plywood throughout. Polymer composite appears only where necessary: the tires, handlebars, and hubs. In all, the bike is reported to weigh less than 3 kg, which does sound pretty light. However, the company’s claim of “the most lightweight kids balance bike in the world” falls a bit short considering the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/12/03/specialized-builds-their-lightest-bike-yet-the-4-63lb-hotwalk-carbon-balance-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Specialized Hotwalk carbon</a> checks in at 4.63lbs (2.1kg) and the<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/09/05/strider-bikes-st-r/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Strider ST-R</a> balance bike weighs 5.6lbs (2.55kg). However, the Choppy does get pretty close in weight for a lot less money.</p><h2>Pricing and availability</h2><p>STUM Inc. just launched Choppy on Indiegogo. Early pledge packages for the bike start at $150. The first round of orders will roll out as early as September 2021.</p><p>To put a pledge in, peddle over to <a href=\"https://www.indiegogo.com/projects/choppy-wooden-balance-bike-for-kids\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Choppy’s Indiegogo page</a>.</p><blockquote data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/CStwLAkCAQJ/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" data-instgrm-version=\"13\"></blockquote></section></article></main></div></div>","author":"Jilli Cluff","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b30acb866dca07834b7e98915c9b5dbf79b557cb5b17f87bc9bb77d6980de93c","category":"Cycling"}